class Solution {
    public int[] transformArray(int[] nums) {
        int count0 = 0, count1 = 0;
        for (int num : nums) {
            if (num % 2 == 0) {
                count0++;
            } else {
                count1++;
            }
        }
        int[] result = new int[nums.length];
        int index = 0;
        while (count0-- > 0) {
            result[index++] = 0;
        }
        while (count1-- > 0) {
            result[index++] = 1;
        }
        return result;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1) // excluding the output array
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution directly counts the number of 0s and 1s after transformation, then constructs the result array. This approach avoids the actual sorting, making it efficient.
